                        <div class="Post-inner">
                            <p align="left"><img src="images/prescription-label.jpg" width="650" height="23" /><img src="images/office2.jpg" width="650" height="268" /></p>
<p class="style4">Welcome  to Rapid Recovery Hyperbarics in California. We have been providing excellence  in Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) to all ages and conditions for over 19  years. <br />
                              <br />
                              At Rapid Recovery Hyperbarics we maintain only the highest standard in  Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy. Hyperbaric oxygen therapy (HBOT) is the  therapeutic use of oxygen at a level higher than normal atmospheric  pressure.  Hyperbaric Oxygen therapy  (HBOT) is an amazing, safe, non-invasive treatment. <br />
</p>
<p align="center" class="style6">&quot;Off Label&quot; Internationally Accepted Conditions Are:</p>
<ul type="square" class="style4">
                              <li><em>Autism</em></li>
                              <li><em>Wound Care</em></li>
                              <li><em>Stroke</em></li>
                              <li><em>Cerebral Palsy / C.P.</em></li>
                              <li><em>Closed Head Injury</em></li>
                              <li><em>Reflex Sympathetic Dystrophy       / R.S.D. / C.R.P.S</em></li>
                              <li><em>Lyme Disease</em></li>
                              <li><em>Multiple       Sclerosis / M.S.</em></li>
                              <li><em>Traumatic Brain Injury</em> / T.B.I.</li>
                              <li><em>Post-Surgical Healing</em></li>
                              <li><em>Diabetic Conditions</em></li>
                              <li><em>Spinal injury and sports       injury</em> / Conditioning Therapy</li>
                              <li>Migraine / Headaches</li>
                              <li>Amputation Recovery</li>
                              <li>Macular Degeneration</li>
                              <li>Auto Immune Diseases</li>
                              <li><em>HBOT is considered investigational for the above listed disorders</em></li>
                              <li>Other categories are constanly being added for experimental off label Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy.</li>
</ul>
<p align="center" class="style7">FDA Approved Conditions:<br />
</p>
<ul type="square" class="style4">
  <li>Air or Gas Embolism</li>
  <li><em>Exceptional Blood Loss/Anemia</em></li>
  <li><em>Carbon Monoxide and Smoke Inhalation</em></li>
  <li><em>Carbon Monoxide Poisoning Complicated By Cyanide Poisoning</em></li>
  <li><em>Crush Injury</em></li>
  <li><em>Decompression Sickness (The Bends)</em></li>
  <li><em>Clostridal Myositis and Myonecrosis / Gas Gangrene</em></li>
  <li><em>Necrotizing Soft Tissue Infections</em></li>
  <li><em>Intracranial Abscess / Osteomyelitis</em></li>
  <li><em>Complications of Radiation Therapy / Radiation Tissue Damage</em></li>
  <li><em>Skin Grafts and Flaps</em></li>
  <li><em>Thermal Burns</em></li>
  <li><em>Sudden Hearing Loss / Tinnitus</em></li>
</ul>
<p class="style4">Clients have come from  all over the world for therapy at Rapid Recovery and we have witnessed amazing  results with FDA approved conditions. Please don’t hesitate to contact us with any questions. Our goal is to  assist you in finding the most successful therapeutic route for you or your loved  one.<br />
                              <strong><em><br />
                          “At Rapid  Recovery Hyperbarics our mission is to provide safe, private, gentle, and  productive Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy for children and adults.”</em></strong></p>
<div align="center" class="style4"><strong><em>
                              <hr size="2" width="100%" align="center" />
                            </em></strong></div>
                            <p class="style4">The field  of Hyperbaric Oxygen is emerging, increasing in growth, utilization, and  availability. In the last several years, an ever-increasing percentage of the  public has been afforded the opportunity to benefit from this safe and  productive application for enhanced health.<br />
                              <br />
                              Hyperbaric  Oxygen is widely used throughout the world and is gaining recognition at an  astonishing rate. Most physicians and the public perception of HBOT is limited  to the use in diving complications. However, this is about to change as patient  involvement in health emerges and new studies arise.<br />
  <strong><em><br />
  “Oxygen is an essential ingredient of life, maintaining  quality, helping the immune system while promoting the revasculation of  ischemic tissue. Restriction of vital oxygen levels (hypoxia) accelerates  degenerative conditions. Most hypoxic tissues require Hyperbaric pressure to  achieve a significant increase in oxygen delivery.”</em></strong> <strong><em>(“The Life is in the Blood”</em></strong> <strong>)</strong><br />
  <strong><em><br />
  “Hyperbaric  Medicine will undoubtedly emerge as a major preventative measure of the 21st  century…” <br /> 
  (Dr. Hooper M.D., The Spinal Rehabilitation Group)</em></strong><br />
                              <br />
                              Clinical  experience continues to demonstrate the therapeutic and economic advantages of  Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy. Experience shows that the public is increasingly  involved with their health and treatment plan. The informed patient will  intelligently investigate current evidence and a range of options, and require  to be a part of the decision making process.<br />
                              <br />
                              We trust that this website will be  an inspiration to everyone who needs it.<br />
                              <br />
                              We warmly welcome you!<br />
  <em><br />
  Susan Rodriguez C.H.T.</em><br />
  <em>Patrick Rodriguez C.H.T., E.M.T.</em><br />
  <em>Founders</em></p>
